description:
Spirits known as kamui are thrown into chaos when the sacred spirit Okikurumi is taken from Atsuma's village, and the imbalance threatens to destroy Earth. Infused with the spirit of an ancient sword, Atsuma must leave his village to reclaim Okikurumi.

He encounters NOA, an organization of youths who wield the power of the kamui, and who may hold the key to Okikurumi. Atsuma is recruited into NOA by Sumire, a young woman with an empty soul who yearns for a miracle. Atsuma and his new companions must work together to find Okikurumi before the world is destroyed.
name: Vol. 1

description:
When Atsuma defeats an atanan and saves a NOA cadet, Anzu, he gains both unwanted fame and a follower. Despite an unwillingness to respond to Anzu's admiration, Atsuma relents to taking her to NOA's annual ball.

But there are some who see Anzu as a way to strike Atsuma where he is most weak. With NOA's annual ball approaching, their plan could unleash a devastating reaction.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Although Atsuma is distraught by the horror he caused on the night of the annual ball, Sumire convinces him to continue with his mission. With Shui's help, they are determined to find out the truth behind NOA, even if it means confronting General Shiki. However, Shiki is just a pawn in a much larger scheme with dark connections to Atsuma's own past.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 10: The Chosen Path
  • Chapter 11: Fabricated Reality
  • Chapter 12: Beyond the Visible
  • Chapter 13: Transfiguration
  • Chapter 14: My Wish
name: Vol. 3

description:
Utsuho's plan comes to fruition as Okikurumi begins to grow, swallowing up all living things around it. The spirit Kojomaru, now separate from Atsuma, finds his host broken and beaten in the ruins of NOA.

With Utsuho's plan building momentum, there seems to be no hope. But the past comes to light and Utsuho's connection with Atsuma is finally revealed.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 15: Overlapping Shadows
  • Chapter 16: Destruction
  • Chapter 17: White Voice
  • Chapter 18: Red Flower
  • Chapter 19: Dark Vision
name: Vol. 4

description:
While Atsuma lies near death at the secret NOA hideout, Sumire and Kojomaru realize they have a common goal. Together, they return to the destroyed NOA headquarters to seek out Utsuho and find Okikurumi. But before they can continue, Sumire must confront Shiki.

Meanwhile, Yanagi and the reprogrammed Hyde hunt down Atsuma, in an attempt to get rid of him once and for all.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 20: Contract
  • Chapter 21: Holding On
  • Chapter 22: Invisible Chains
  • Chapter 23: What Is Gained
  • Chapter 24: What Can Be Done
name: Vol. 5

description:
Atsuma has chosen to stand and fight back against Yanagi and Hyde, that is, if his body can hold out that long. But when he manages to tap into a new form of tohsu, both he and Kojomaru are affected.

Meanwhile, Kojomaru's search for his sword body continues, but the presence of Sumire so close to Okikurumi causes an unexpected awakening.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 25: Reason To Resist
  • Chapter 26: Return
  • Chapter 27: Light
  • Chapter 28: Distant Love
name: Vol. 6

description:
NOA is destroyed, its members scattered or consumed by Okikurumi. Still, Atsuma is compelled to return to the ruins of the only place he ever felt kindness and friendship.

Aika has escaped from Okikurumi, but where is Shui? As she struggles to connect with Lady Sumire, Shiki confronts Atsuma, who now possesses a strange new power, a power which could destroy him.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 29: Omen of Awakening
  • Chapter 30: For One's Own
  • Chapter 31: Strength
  • Chapter 32: Choice
name: Vol. 7

description:
Atsuma has tapped into his own power, and now hopes to use it to save the world and his friends in NOA.

But first, he and his allies must fight their way into Utsuho’s stronghold. While Atsuma and Shui head towards the root of Okikurumi, Sumire and Kojomaru confront Utsuho.

But neither Okikurumi nor Utsuho will fall easily, and there are still secrets to be revealed.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 33: Conflicting Paths
  • Chapter 34: Fangs That Bite
  • Chapter 35: Reunion
  • Chapter 36: Awakening
  • Chapter 37: Kojomaru
name: Vol. 8

description:
Time is running out. Having battled their way into Utsuho’s stronghold, Atsuma and his friends must fight to save both NOA and the world. Kojomaru has taken a new form, one determined to destroy Atsuma and Shui, but is it Kojomaru who needs saving? Meanwhile Shiki faces off against Utsuho, and the wounded Yanagi is confronted by a devastating revelation.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 38: Higher God
  • Chapter 39: Tears
  • Chapter 40: Sway
  • Chapter 41: Shared Vision
  • Chapter 42: Parting Ways
name: Vol. 9

description:
Atsuma continues his struggle into the depths of NOA—but if his friends have anything to say about it, he isn’t going alone! When Utsuho sets off a deadly trap, reaching him will prove to be more difficult than any of them could have anticipated.

Meanwhile, Sumire and Shiki have discovered the secret of Utsuho's deadly contract…but will they be able to warn Atsuma before the final battle can begin?
name: Vol. 10

description: Originally Published by Dark Horse Comics as DANGER UNLIMITED #1-4, Babe #1-4 & BABE 2 #1-2.
name: TPB

description:
The Kid

Billy has changed, and not for the better. Dark secrets and mysteries now surround the teen-aged gunslinger, and something haunts his nightmares.

The Disc containing all the incriminating evidence on the Administration has been taken. They will do whatever it takes to get it back before their secrets are exposed.

This issue - Two Hitmen are contracted out to retrieve the disc. Once in their possession, they quickly realize that they are dead men the moment they turn the disc over so they decide to run.
name: Book One

description: Ariel Chylde is the girl cursed to become any of the creatures from her many Nightmares. But have the shadows circled all her life? Now we go deeper. Into her past. Into her dreams. Where fears roam, and truth is never a friend.
name: TPB

description: Lansdale lovers rejoice, the team that brought you The Drive-In is back for this sequel to one of horror(s most beloved books, The Drive-In 2! Artist Andres Guinaldo returns to bring to life the next chapter of the story about a group of friends who wanted nothing more than to enjoy a day at the movies. The final showdown with Popalong is here and the casualties mount even higher This series continues the action, madness, and razor-sharp dialogue Lansdale fans the world over have been waiting for! Available in regular and wraparound covers by Guinaldo.

Few names in the art world invoke passion like that of Joseph Michael Linsner. A maverick phenomenon, Linsner has been painting visions of Heavenly women and Hellish demons since he introduced his personal tribute to the Goddess, Dawn, in 1989. This much-anticipated volume collects 176 pages of Linsner's very best work, with over a dozen previously unpublished paintings. Also featured is a special "how-to" section, in which Linsner details the creation of a Dawn painting from start to finish. More than simply pin-up art, Linsner's work illuminates a complex personal mythology, rife with its own language of symbols.

Ever wanted to go to Heaven, Hell, and beyond? Linsner's art will take you there.
name: HC/SC

volume.name: The Art of Joseph Michael Linsner

description:
All art is lushly rendered in full-color by Joseph Michael Linsner, creator of Dawn. A Linsner Girl is one with a sparkle in her eye, a saucy pose and plenty of beautiful skin. Girls & Goddesses features Dawn, Dark Ivory, Sinful Suzi and many other gorgeous Linsner pin-up girls collected together for the first time! Showcasing page after page of previously unpublished work, this is a must for all lovers of tasteful pin-up and true beauty, both earthly and divine. Collected for the first time are Linsner's finest glimpses of joyful heaven walking on earth—his Girls & Goddesses.

Collecting literally dozens of previously unpublished works, this volume is a must for all lovers of true beauty, both earthly and divine.
name: The Pin-Up Art of Joseph Michael Linsner

description:
Faction 1 features a ripping collection of some of New Zealand's best comic creators, including Greg Broadmore, (concept designer at Weta Workshop who worked on District 9, Elysium and other blockbusters), Ant Sang (Bro'Town and Shaolin Burning), Roger Langridge (Popeye, The Muppet Show Comics, Knuckles the Malevolent Nun), Karl Wills, Jonathan King and many more.

Stories range from deep space, to the Arctic Circle and far future. The book is 61 pages and includes a foreword by Ben Stenbeck (Baltimore).
name: Vol. 1

description: Reprinting the RAREST issue of Femforce ever produced- Femforce #16, originally published in 1988, featuring the She-Cat origin tie-in story, “Barefoot And Malevolent”. Due to a format and printer change after Femforce issues #15 , FF #16 was heavily undered ordered and sold out quickly. It is finally available in this reprint edition.
